# Python source and tests

## Lakehouse package (`src/laken/`)

- `lakehouse.py` — `Lakehouse` facade; picks local vs Fabric backend.
- `local.py` — parquet files under a configurable root (default `./lakehouse`).
- `fabric.py` — Delta tables + Spark; expects Fabric notebook runtime for integration.
- `frames.py` — coerce between pandas, polars, and Spark by `as_=` parameter.
- `paths.py`, `types.py`, `protocol.py` — shared path parsing and protocols.

## Deploy package (`src/laken/deploy/`)

- Thin orchestration; CLI lives in `cli.py`.
- `build.py` — subprocess `uv build` from project cwd.
- `fabric_client.py` — Azure token + Fabric staging/publish HTTP.
- `config.py` — `.env` / env vars and `require_project_root()`.
- `project.py`, `wheel.py` — read `pyproject.toml` metadata and resolve `dist/*.whl`.

## Tests (`tests/`)

- Shared fixtures in `tests/conftest.py`: `lakehouse`, `sample_pandas`, `sample_polars`, `sample_df` (parametrized pandas/polars).
- Mirror module layout: root tests for lakehouse/frames/paths; `tests/deploy/` for deploy modules.
- Prefer existing fixture patterns over new test harnesses.

## Verification

After edits: `uv sync` (if deps changed) → `uv run ruff check` → scoped or full `uv run pytest` per area touched.
